theorem interior_inter_closure_eq_empty_of_disjoint {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hDisj : Disjoint (A : Set X) B) :
    interior (A : Set X) ∩ closure (B : Set X) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hxIntA, hxClB⟩
    -- Obtain an open neighborhood `U` of `x` contained in `A`.
    rcases (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).1 hxIntA with ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_subA⟩
    -- Since `x ∈ closure B`, the neighborhood `U` meets `B`.
    have hUB_nonempty : (U ∩ (B : Set X)).Nonempty := by
      have := (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClB U hU_open hxU
      simpa using this
    rcases hUB_nonempty with ⟨y, hyU, hyB⟩
    -- Then `y ∈ A ∩ B`, contradicting disjointness.
    have hyA : (y : X) ∈ (A : Set X) := hU_subA hyU
    have hContr : False := (Set.disjoint_left.1 hDisj) hyA hyB
    exact hContr.elim
  · exact Set.empty_subset _

theorem isClosed_closure_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    IsClosed (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))) := by
  simpa using
    (isClosed_closure :
      IsClosed (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))))
